The directory is empty, so there's no existing project to modify. Here's the implementation pattern you need:

**1. Create `Middleware/ApiExceptionHandler.cs`:**

```csharp
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Diagnostics;
using Microsoft.AspNetCore.Mvc;

namespace YourApp.Middleware;

internal sealed class ApiExceptionHandler(ILogger<ApiExceptionHandler> logger)
    : IExceptionHandler
{
    public async ValueTask<bool> TryHandleAsync(
        HttpContext httpContext,
        Exception exception,
        CancellationToken cancellationToken)
    {
        var (statusCode, title) = exception switch
        {
            KeyNotFoundException => (StatusCodes.Status404NotFound, "Not Found"),
            ArgumentException => (StatusCodes.Status400BadRequest, "Bad Request"),
            InvalidOperationException => (StatusCodes.Status409Conflict, "Conflict"),
            _ => (0, (string?)null)
        };

        if (statusCode == 0)
            return false; // Default handler returns 500 with no sensitive details

        logger.LogWarning(exception, "Handled API exception: {Title}", title);

        httpContext.Response.StatusCode = statusCode;
        await httpContext.Response.WriteAsJsonAsync(new ProblemDetails
        {
            Status = statusCode,
            Title = title,
            Detail = title,
            Instance = httpContext.Request.Path
        }, cancellationToken);

        return true;
    }
}
```

**2. Register in `Program.cs`:**

```csharp
builder.Services.AddExceptionHandler<ApiExceptionHandler>();
builder.Services.AddProblemDetails();

var app = builder.Build();

app.UseExceptionHandler();  // Catches all unhandled exceptions
app.UseStatusCodePages();   // Converts bare status codes to Problem Details

// ... your endpoints below
```

**How it works:**

| Exception | Status | Response |
|-----------|--------|----------|
| `KeyNotFoundException` | 404 | `{"title":"Not Found","status":404,...}` |
| `ArgumentException` | 400 | `{"title":"Bad Request","status":400,...}` |
| `InvalidOperationException` | 409 | `{"title":"Conflict","status":409,...}` |
| Anything else | 500 | Generic Problem Details (no stack trace/message leaked) |

The `IExceptionHandler` pipeline runs globally — no per-endpoint `try-catch` needed. Returning `false` for unknown exceptions lets the default `UseExceptionHandler` middleware produce a safe 500 response using `AddProblemDetails()`.
